Salcedia coquilhati
Alluaud, 1932: 3; 
Csiki 1933
: 641; 
Alluaud 1935
: 19; 
Burgeon 1935
: 159; 
Reichardt 1975
: 103; 1932, 
Dostal 1993
: 121; 
Lorenz 2005
: 155.

(Fig. 
84
). Known from several localities along the course of the Congo River and at the mouth of the river Tshuapa. Some of the specimens were collected at light. The historic name Coquilhatville refers to the city today called Mbandaka, that of Stanleyville to Kisangani, and Brazzaville to Kinshasa.
